1.00	Peter_Ramus	Petrus Ramus	Petrus Ramus (or Pierre de la Ramée) (Anglicized to Peter Ramus) (1515 – 26 August 1572) was an influential French humanist, logician, and educational reformer. A Protestant convert, he was killed during the St. Bartholomew's Day Massacre.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/Petrus_Ramus.jpg/200px-Petrus_Ramus.jpg
